cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.COMM, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper investigates the performance of a two-way relay network under the finite blocklength regime, which is a topic closely related to information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper studies a three-node relay network, which is a typical networking scenario. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the performance of different relay schemes and derives closed-form expressions, which are related to system modeling and control. 
4. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper investigates the performance of a communication system with a relay, which is a core topic in communication and networking. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the concept of short-packet communications may have applications in multimedia systems, such as real-time video streaming.
